'''Dot Farley''' (February 6, 1881 &ndash; May 2, 1971)<ref>[http://www.findagrave.com/cgi-bin/fg.cgi?page=gsr&GSfn=dot+&GSmn=&GSln=farley&GSbyrel=all&GSby=&GSdyrel=all&GSdy=&GScntry=0&GSst=0&GSst=0&GSgrid=&df=all&GSob=n Dot Farley; findagrave.com] Retrieved September 9, 2016</ref> was an American film actress. She appeared in 280 films between 1910 and 1950. Mainly known for her roles in short comedies, prolific with [[Mack Sennett]] in the silent days; she was later notable as the mother-in-law of [[Edgar Kennedy]] in most of his series of short films at the [[RKO Pictures|RKO]] studios. She was born in [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]] and died in [[South Pasadena, California]].
