{{Use Indian English|date=August 2018}}
'''Vanitha Rangaraju-Ramanan''' (born 1970) is an [[India]]n animator who works for [[DreamWorks Animation]]. Rangaraju was part of the team that won a 2002 [[Academy Award for Best Animated Feature]] for movie ''[[Shrek]]'', for which she was credited as Lighting Technical Director.

==Early life and career==
Rangaraju was born 1970 in [[Tiruchirappalli]], where she went to school and graduated with a [[Bachelor of Architecture]] from the [[Regional Engineering College, Tiruchirappalli]]. In 1996, she pursued Master's program at the [[University of Texas at Austin]] followed by an intership at [[Industrial Light & Magic]] in 1998. Since then she has been with DreamWorks Animation. Some of her movie credits are ''Shrek 2'', ''Madagascar'', ''Shrek the Third'', ''Madagascar: Escape to Africa'' and ''Puss in Boots''.

